cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it deals with the problem of ego-motion estimation using LiDAR and IMU sensors. It could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it involves point-cloud matching and pose estimation. The use of non-linear optimization methods suggests that it could also be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the fusion of LiDAR and IMU sensors for ego-motion estimation is a common problem in the field of Autonomous Systems (cs.SY), making it a possible sub-category as well.
